99. Ille tenet speculum] The miri-ors of the ancients were of metal, though there may have been glass mirrors at this time, but they were of inferior quality. They were only made for the hand, and were usually held by slaves before their mistress (see Dict. Ant.). This man holds it for himself, and Juvenal says it was the iden- tical mirror in which Otho had looked at himself, and of which this person had rob- bed him, which is a jest.
